a bomb exploded at a us paint 
company in manila early monday the eighth blast at an american 
company in a week police said 
they said the explosion caused no casualties but broke windows 
and damaged a concrete wall of the fuller obrien factory in 
suburban mandaluyong 
col ernesto diokno said rebel soldiers may have been behind the 
bombing because c4 plastic explosive issued only to the military 
was used 
seven us companies have been bombed since wednesday mondays 
bombing was the 34th in the capital since august when the spate of 
explosions began 
government offices and companies owned by chinesefilipino 
business people were targeted in the last two months 
authorities said the bombings are meant to frighten foreign 
investors and destabilize the economy undermining the government 
of president corazon aquino 
