the government rounded up japaneseamericans in 1942 after war 
roke out with japan distrusting their loyalty germanamericans 
did not receive such treatment 
about 120000 people were forced to abandon nearly all their 
possessions and were confined at 10 camps most in remote inland 
areas of the west and at scattered hospitals and sanitariums 
